i## Installing and Enabling SPDY		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iSPDY is a network protocol spearheaded by Google. It allows		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
imultiplexing multiple data streams within a single SSL connection.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iWithout SPDY, browsers open multiple SSL connections simultaneously to		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iload resources. Often, mid-page load, the browser discovers additional		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ineeded resources and must open new connections, causing delays. SPDY		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ieliminates this overhead by enabling concurrent downloads within one		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iSSL connection.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Update your nginx version. The default nginx in Debian repositories		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  lacks SPDY support. Replace it with `nginx-full` :		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    apt-get install nginx-full		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i- Edit your nginx configuration file. Change:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    listen 443 ssl;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  to:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    listen 443 ssl spdy;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  Done.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
